b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48059.htm)  [Next](sbe48061.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n27\\. And thus also, because (thus only) the designation of the beings, and so\non, being the (four) feet is possible.\n\nThe text, moreover, designates the Gayatri as having four feet, after having\nreferred to the beings, the earth, the body, and the heart; now this has a\nsense only if it is Brahman, which here is called Gayatri.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 28. If it be said that Brahman is not recognised...](sbe48061.htm)\n\n'